snippet: Bama Covered is believed to be the only group doing enrollment for insurance under the Affordable Care Act that is made up solely of college students.
abstract: About 600 student volunteers from a dozen colleges in Alabama have been trained to help enroll people for insurance under Pres Obama's health care reform law; all-volunteer group is believed to be the only one doing enrollment entirely made up of college students, and founders hope if they can succeed in the red state, their effort will be replicable across the country.
lead_paragraph: Bama Covered is believed to be the only group doing enrollment for insurance under the Affordable Care Act that is made up solely of college students.
